<h1>€ddie$</h1>
<h3>Year one</h3>
<b>In year one 1 €ddie$ is priced at (21 EUR + 21 USD)* 1 + 21% VAT + 21% INFLATION. Each year this formula goes up with 21% INFLATION, just like the rings on a tree it keeps growing annually.<b>

<h3>Year two</h3>
<b><a href="https://algoexplorer.io/tx/YYRM2TA3JMBBWH4JBVRGK4G6IECRDUOIJCJJKG2WKLUPKA743FOA"  target="_blank" style="background-color:orange">One year after the first €ddie$ is created</a> the price is now ((21 EUR + 21 USD)* 1 + 21% + 21%) + 21% <b>

<h3>Year three</h3>
<b>Two years after the first €ddie$ is created the price is now (((21 EUR + 21 USD)* 1 + 21% + 21%) + 21%) + 21% etc.<b>


  <h3>Inflation</h3>
  <b>€ddie$ price increase is a reaction to currency inflation, €ddie$ are deflationary by nature.<b>


